  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nThis happens only when the App is in the state - \r\nlogged out after being signed in previously and user having tried to enter a wrong pwd. \r\n\r\nIn this situation, when the user tries to use the seed phrase to re-encrypt a new pwd, they find that the UI is stuck & they cannot re-encrypt the new keys when they hit `Create Pwd` button at the end of the Re-encrypt flow with the following log :\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/95302135/158075937-085ca67b-cc15-4b18-bd4b-a73acdb50bcf.png)\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce \r\n- Sign in to an account\r\n- Once signed in, go to `Settings` and click `Sign out & Quit` to sign out.\r\n- Launch the app again and entera wrong Pwd to simulate user forgetting their Pwd\r\n- Click the drop down arrow beside the account name\r\n- Click the `Add another existing key` button to enter the existing saved seed phrase for this account (_**or another account**_)\r\n- Hit `Re-encrypt your keys` button\r\n- Enter the new Pwd and hit `Create Pwd`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nUser is able to create a new Pwd\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/95302135/157882689-c8483702-26bf-4ad8-94ae-f4f67b7a0d9f.mp4\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: Master\r\n",
